   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Water - crisis - Mentally Challenged children</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Project Site  - village in South East Bangalore - India.  Water shortage exists due to urbanization affecting Gerizim&apos;s Boys Home waterless for the past 4 months.  The beneficiaries of this project are more than 60 orphaned &amp; Mentally Challenged teenagers.  This crisis forces us buy water everyday shelling a lot of money meant for the child care ($10 /load /day) - a great cause of concern. The issue could be sorted out by digging up/ deepening the borewells costing approximately $10,000/-</narrative>
  </description>
